# The mesh() Factory

mesh() combines geometry and material into a THREE.Mesh in one call:

```
const { mesh, sphere } = ctx;

const ball = mesh(
  sphere(0.6),
  { color: 0x4466ff, roughness: 0.4 }
);
ball.position.set(0, 1, 0);
ctx.add(ball);
```

The returned object is a standard THREE.Mesh — set position, rotation, scale, and userData just as you would in plain Three.js.

Animate it in update():

```
export function update(ctx, dt) {
  ball.rotation.y += dt;
  ball.position.y = Math.sin(ctx.elapsed) * 0.5;
}
```
